	v6eval-env

This script creates a virtual environment for testing the IPv6 stack of the
Linux kernel using v6eval from the TAHI project[1].

Two virtual machines are created and connected according to this topology:

        192.168.33.1
    tap0----br0----tap2
     |              |
     |              |   
    eth0           eth0
    VM1            VM2
    eth1           eth1
     |              |
     |              |
    tap1----br1----tap3
       192.168.34.1











  [1] - www.tahi.org

